juniFileXferMIB.name: juniFileXferMIB

revisions.description: Replaced Unisphere names with Juniper names.

Key revisions include: o Obsoleted juniFileXferRemoteUserName. o Obsoleted juniFileXferRemoteUserPassword. o Added juniFileXferRouterName. o Added juniFileXferCopyRunningCfgFailed(9) to juniFileXferStatus.
Initial version of this MIB module.

juniFileXferTable.name: juniFileXferTable
juniFileXferTable.description: A list of entries which describe file transfers.

juniFileXferTableEntry.name: juniFileXferTableEntry
juniFileXferTableEntry.description: A description of a particular file transfer entry.

juniFileXferIndex.name: juniFileXferIndex
juniFileXferIndex.description: A unique index used to identify this entry.

juniFileXferDirection.name: juniFileXferDirection
juniFileXferDirection.description: Specifies the direction of the file transfer.

juniFileXferFileType.name: juniFileXferFileType
juniFileXferFileType.description: Specifies the file type of the file transfer.

juniFileXferRemoteFileName.name: juniFileXferRemoteFileName
juniFileXferRemoteFileName.description: The full path name of the source/destination file on the remote system.

juniFileXferRemoteUserName.name: juniFileXferRemoteUserName
juniFileXferRemoteUserName.description: The user name to use when requesting the file transfer to/from the remote system. This object has been obsoleted. Use the enterprise host mib in order to configure the username.

juniFileXferRemoteUserPassword.name: juniFileXferRemoteUserPassword
juniFileXferRemoteUserPassword.description: The password to use when requesting the file transfer to/from the remote system. When read, this object returns a zero string. Note that, for security reasons, some FTP servers may insist on a non-zero length user password. This object has been obsoleted. Use the enterprise host MIB in order to configure the password.

juniFileXferLocalFileName.name: juniFileXferLocalFileName
juniFileXferLocalFileName.description: The local file name to transfer or to create as a result of an incoming transfer.

juniFileXferProtocol.name: juniFileXferProtocol
juniFileXferProtocol.description: Specifies the file transfer protocol type.

juniFileXferStatus.name: juniFileXferStatus
juniFileXferStatus.description: The status of the file transfer.

juniFileXferRowStatus.name: juniFileXferRowStatus
juniFileXferRowStatus.description: The row status object controls the creation/deletion of rows in this table. Its semantics are the same as those for the RowStatus textual convention specified for SNMPv2. Setting this object to createAndGo(4) is allowed. If required objects are missing, the agent will create the row and set its status to notReady(3). If all of the required objects are present and valid, the agent will create the row, set it to active and commence the file transfer. Upon completion of the file transfer, the agent will set the rowStatus to notInService(2), indicating that the row is valid and useable by a management client. To commence another transfer, a management client should set the rowStatus to active(1). Setting this object to createAndWait(5) causes an entry to be created with juniFileXferRowStatus value of notInService(2) if all of the required objects are present and valid. Or, if some of the required objects are missing or invalid, the agent will create the row and sets its status to notReady(3). Setting this object to active(1) causes the transfer to start for the given row. Objects within the row cannot be modified once a row has been set to active(1), Setting this object to destroy(6) causes the corresponding row to be deleted. Note that only a single instance of a row can be active at at any given moment, although several rows can exist in the table.

juniFileXferTimeStamp.name: juniFileXferTimeStamp
juniFileXferTimeStamp.description: The value of sysUpTime at the last status change for this entry.

juniFileXferRouterName.name: juniFileXferRouterName
juniFileXferRouterName.description: The name of the router to be used when resolving the hostname portion of the juniFileXferRemoteFileName object. If this object contains an invalid or empty value, the default router will be used.

juniFileXferTrapEnabled.name: juniFileXferTrapEnabled
juniFileXferTrapEnabled.description: An indication of whether the juniFileXferTrap trap is enabled.

juniFileXferTrap.name: juniFileXferTrap
juniFileXferTrap.description: An indication that the status associated with a particular file transfer entry has changed.

juniFileXferCompliance1.name: juniFileXferCompliance1

juniFileXferCompliance2.name: juniFileXferCompliance2
juniFileXferCompliance2.description: The compliance statement for entities that implement the Juniper file transfer MIB.

juniFileXferGroup1.name: juniFileXferGroup1
juniFileXferGroup1.description: Obsolete collection of objects providing management of file transfers in a Juniper product. This group became obsolete when remote user information was removed and juniFileXferRouterName was added.

juniFileXferGroup2.name: juniFileXferGroup2
juniFileXferGroup2.description: A collection of objects providing management of file transfers in a Juniper product.

juniFileXferTrapGroup.name: juniFileXferTrapGroup
juniFileXferTrapGroup.description: A management notification pertaining to file transfers.
